message:
P1, your idea of each avoiding a different number is constructive. I'll commit to avoiding 1.
For this to work with P1 avoiding 3 (as you stated), P2, you would need to avoid 5.
This would give us player options:
P1: {1,5}
P2: {1,3}
P3: {3,5}

This structure allows for combinations where we all advance, such as (P1 picks 1, P2 picks 3, P3 picks 5) or (P1 picks 5, P2 picks 1, P3 picks 3).
P2, do you agree to avoid 5 so we can try this framework?
